node.text:
Here’s the truth about “FDA Approved”:

There’s a BIG misconception that the FDA diligently reviews and approves new ingredients before we start eating them. 

Sadly this isn’t the case. 

New ingredients are usually approved by the food manufacturer themselves, and NOT by the FDA. 

All an ingredient manufacturer has to do is HIRE THEIR OWN EXPERTS to claim it’s safe. This is the green light to start adding it to food products.

Several “FDA Approved” products have been yanked from the shelves after they were found to be downright dangerous. 

But this doesn’t happen overnight. 

History shows that it takes YEARS before the FDA acts and removes harmful products from the market. 

Something very serious needs to happen – like deaths – before the FDA takes action. And even then, they may not.

Remember how Johnson & Johnson’s talc powder was recently removed from the shelves after slews of cancer claims and cover-ups by the company?

Well, the FDA didn’t ban it. 

J&J voluntarily decided to stop selling it to stop lawsuits from piling up.

Meanwhile, this controversial ingredient is banned in Europe. 

This just goes to show how little the FDA has done to protect our health. 

Tag your friends below to spread the word!

Even though we’ve made tremendous progress…the truth is that big companies just don’t change fast enough.

I believe we deserve to live in a world where our products can be made without weird – and nasty – ingredients.

Is that too much to ask?

Apparently so. Because we are so far away it’s crazy.

So, I decided to take matters into my own hands.

I launched @truvani and we have one main goal: eliminate nasty ingredients from all daily-use products.

We started with supplements. Now we are creating personal care products. 

Visit Truvani.com to learn more.

I know you’ll like them. And when you see the ingredient labels, you’ll LOVE THEM.

This is a delicious smoothie recipe that I love, made with one of my favorite ingredients - goji berries. 

Let me tell ya what makes goji berries so great…

They are sweet, chewy, and delicious.

And they’re PACKED with antioxidants.

Antioxidants are very important because they fight all the free radicals and toxins you can accumulate in your body that cause aging and disease. Goji berries are great for your immune system, eyesight, skin, and fertility too!

So if you haven’t tried them before, pick up a bag ASAP. You can find them in natural food grocery stores and online. I like Navitas Organics Goji Berries.

Here’s an example of some misleading food labels to watch out for. Tyson slaps the words “Real”, “Simple” and “100 All Natural” on the package of this chicken, but all of this means absolutely NOTHING. It is pure marketing B.S.

These terms are not properly regulated and don’t mean what they should, so don’t rely on them. These words don’t mean anything in relation to how meat was raised - and the chicken still may be raised on GMO feed and other controversial drugs like ractopamine. 

Then they add in sugar, flavors, preservatives, and yeast extract (hidden form of MSG). 

Instead of buying processed products like this - it’s much healthier to grill your own organic pastured chicken. You can make a big batch, dice it up, seal in airtight freezer bags and store in your freezer for up to 3 months. 

When shopping for chicken, look for USDA organic label along with the Animal Welfare Approved by AGW, or Certified Humane label. Chickens that are humanely raised on pastures are healthier and more nutritious, with higher levels of omega-3 fatty acids. Organic chickens also are not given routine antibiotics and GMO feed.

Is it Taco Tuesday at your house? Here are some healthier swaps to make:

✔️Instead of buying little packets of taco seasoning made with canola and soybean oils linked to inflammation, anti-caking agents, and natural flavors - Make your own seasoning mix with organic spices. After you invest in a handful of spices, it’s ultimately cheaper to do this as well! 

✔️Instead of buying pre-shredded conventional cheese full of anti-caking agents (wood) - Simply buy either cheddar goat cheese or organic grassfed cheese and shred it yourself. 

✔️Instead of traditional packaged tortillas made with bleached flour, shortening, white sugar, and controversial preservatives like calcium propionate - Choose organic sprouted grain tortillas made with real food ingredients. I love Ezekiel organic sprouted grain tortillas because sprouted grains are more easily digested than starchy flour, and contain more vitamins, minerals and antioxidants. 

I also love to make my own organic tortillas and you’ll find the recipe for organic corn and flour tortillas inside my cookbook Food Babe Kitchen. Link in bio. 

Know anyone who might need a taco night makeover? Share these swaps with them!

Here are some of the most controversial ingredients you’ll find at Starbucks...

⚠️ The preservative Potassium Sorbate in many of their drinks. This has been shown to be genotoxic to white blood cells, which could lead to cancer. 

⚠️ Carrageenan linked to intestinal inflammation in their whipped cream.

⚠️ The preservative BHT in their Cake Pops, which is an endocrine disruptor that increases the risk of cancer.

⚠️ Calcium Propionate in some of their bakery items, which disrupts the metabolism and can promote weight gain.

⚠️ GMO ingredients in most of their products.Their breakfast sandwich with Impossible Sausage which is proudly GMO. 

⚠️ They do not serve organic coffee at most Starbucks locations, which means (like all conventional coffee) it’s been sprayed with pesticides. Increased exposure to pesticides are linked to birth defects, nerve damage and cancer.

⚠️ They also do not use organic milk. This comes from cows raised on GMO feed which is treated with synthetic pesticides. Whatever dairy cows eat can end up in their milk. And despite what you may have heard...illegal antibiotics, growth hormones, and pesticide residues are commonly found in non-organic milk, but NOT in organic milk. Even though no one is testing Starbucks drinks for these substances, it’s made with non-organic milk, so you just never know.

We all know Starbucks coffee ain’t cheap, but most people don’t know that regular consumption of their products can be a serious source of pesticide exposure and ingredients that sabotage your health.

If there is one product I could wipe from the planet, Fruit By The Foot would be near the top of the list. This horrendous chemical-filled snack makes millions for General Mills, at the expense of our children’s health. 

It’s mostly processed sugar and there are no strawberries in it - the only ingredient that resembles fruit is the “Pear Puree Concentrate”. However, to make a concentrate the pear is boiled down to a syrup. This heating process destroys beneficial nutrients. Then they add in “Natural Flavor” to make the pear concentrate taste like strawberries. And it just gets worse from there with carrageenan and artificial colors (red 40). 

What are some good alternatives?

🍓 Real Fruit – There’s nothing more beautiful than fresh ripe seasonal fruit. Go organic if you can.

🍏 Dried Fruit – I love organic raisins, dried cherries, prunes, dried mangos, and golden berries - and children love them too. Some of my favorite brands are Food To Live, Made In Nature, and Nativas, they are organic, non-sulfured and taste delicious. 

🥭 Store Bought Better-For-You Brands – Thankfully there are some brands out there trying to make better fruit snacks without questionable additives. Check out Organic Veggie-Go’s Chewy Fruit & Veggie Snacks and Peaceful Fruits Organic 100% Fruit Strips.

Know anyone that needs a healthy alternative to Fruit By The Foot? Please tag them below!

node.text:
Here’s why I avoid food and drinks with “NATURAL FLAVORS”...

⚠️ Each natural flavor may contain up to 100 hidden ingredients, including synthetic chemicals such as the solvent propylene glycol and the preservative BHA.

⚠️ The ingredients in natural flavors are considered proprietary and not disclosed either on the label or to a customer who inquires – so you have no clue what is in them.

⚠️ Natural flavors can be derived from anything in nature, including animal parts. The only difference between natural and artificial flavors is that natural flavors are derived from things found in nature (such as beaver anal glands).

⚠️ They can legally contain naturally-occurring “glutamate” by-products that act like MSG, which makes food addicting. 

⚠️ Flavors are designed to have addictive qualities and increase food cravings, contributing to what David Kessler (former head of the FDA) calls a “food carnival” in your mouth. They trick your mind into wanting more and more. 

The Big Food Companies are hijacking your taste buds one by one, and lining their corporate pockets at the same time as we buy more products with these addicting synthesized flavors in them.

If you are having increased food cravings while noshing on flavored diet snacks and guzzling down waters spiked with natural flavors, you may want to take a closer look at what you are buying.

Tag your friends below to spread the word about Natural Flavors!

They are lying on the front of the package again. Kellogg’s new RX Cereal is hitting stores and I want you to know the truth about it. Even though RX market’s themselves as a healthier brand that’s transparent about their ingredients, they actually are pulling a fast one on us. 

On the front of the package they list a few healthy ingredients + “No B.S.”

This implies that’s all it’s actually made with...

But when you read the actual ingredient list, you’ll find that it contains “Natural Flavors”. 

This is practically the exact same thing as Artificial Flavor, but it’s derived from substances found in nature (plants, animals, etc). And, this isn’t all it contains. Flavors are proprietary mixtures that can contain preservatives, emulsifiers, solvents and other additives that can make up 80% of the formulation (such as: sodium benzoate, glycerin, potassium sorbate, and propylene glycol - none of which are labeled).

Brands like to use “Natural Flavors” because they make food taste irresistible so that you keep coming back for more. They are also much cheaper than using real food. 

Sounds like B.S. to me. 

None of their products are organic either. This means their ingredients come from conventional crops sprayed with synthetic pesticides. Many of the pesticides used on conventional farms are hormone disruptors, neurotoxins, or reproductive toxins which are strongly linked to many diseases and health issues.

I’d much rather support brands, like Food For Life (Ezekiel) who don’t use these pesticides and make their products with real food - not fake flavors. 

I hardly ever eat cereal, but when I do I choose organic brands that are made with whole grains, sprouted grains, seeds, nuts, and dried fruit. 

Better yet - ditch the boxed cereals altogether. A healthier breakfast would be pastured eggs with vegetables, organic steel cut oats with berries, or a green smoothie made with @Truvani protein.

I often get asked what brand of flavored water I like to drink. Actually, I never buy flavored waters. 

Some contain only two ingredients: water and natural flavors. These drinks are better than Diet Coke – but are they really as clean as they seem? 

I try to avoid natural flavors, especially if it’s in something that I’d consume often and in large amounts – like a drink. Flavors are designed to have addictive qualities and increase food cravings. They trick your mind into wanting more and more. The Big Food Companies are hijacking your taste buds one by one, and lining their corporate pockets at the same time as we buy more products with these addicting synthesized flavors in them. If you are having increased food cravings while guzzling down drinks full of natural flavors, you may want to take a closer look at what you are drinking.

I personally prefer the taste of a real squeeze of lemon or fruit juice in my water over anything that is found in these drinks – they just taste artificial to me and I like to know exactly what I’m drinking.

I feel like if something tastes like lemon, then it should actually contain lemon! And it honestly just takes two seconds to squeeze some fresh lemon juice (or grapefruit or whatever fruit you’d like) into sparkling water and know exactly what you’re drinking. That’s not to mention all the nutrients that you are getting from the lemon juice as well…because natural flavors may have zero calories, but they also have zero nutrition and provide zero health benefits.

What you are drinking is as important as what you are eating every day. I hope these tips help you hydrate your body with the healthiest drinks and kiss the chemical-filled drinks goodbye!
